text.data-name: Eating and nutrition is very closely linked to immunity. If you are eating healthy, your body is much more equipped to fight the virus.
text.tspan: Eating and nutrition is very closely linked to
immunity. If you are eating healthy, your body
is much more equipped to fight the virus.

text.data-name: A healthy diet provides minerals and vitamins that are important in ensuring enough immune cells and antibodies, which is important to fight an infection or virus.

text.data-name: Sources of high quality protein, fat, and carbohydrates can maintain a healthy weight, which is important if you get COVID-19 in order to prevent unintended weight loss.

text.data-name: Replacing existing eating habits with higher-quality foods can end up being cheaper as the cost of blood testing is more than the cost of supplements. Overall healthy diets can significantly reduce health care costs in the future.
